### æ€è·¯
Adding from rear to front until both num and k are exhausted.
### Code
```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> addToArrayForm(int[] num, int k) {
        int carry = 0;
        List<Integer> result = new LinkedList<>();
        int i = num.length - 1;
        while (i >= 0 || k > 0) {
            int digitFromK = k % 10;
            int currentDigit = digitFromK + (i >= 0 ? num[i] : 0) + carry;
            if (currentDigit >= 10) {
                carry = 1;
                currentDigit -= 10;
            } else {
                carry = 0;
            }
            result.add(0, currentDigit);
            k /= 10;
            i--;
        }
        if (carry == 1) {
            result.add(0, 1);
        }
        return result;
    }
}
```
