* Space: O(N)

### Idea
* Go forward: record the distance between each letter and the latest c in its left;
* Go backward: update the distance if a letter is closer to the latest c in its right
### Code
```
class Solution {
    public int[] shortestToChar(String s, char c) {
        int[] ans = new int[s.length()];
        int lastIndexC = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == c) {
                ans[i] = 0;
                lastIndexC = i;
            } else if (lastIndexC == Integer.MAX_VALUE) {
                ans[i] = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
            } else {
                ans[i] = i - lastIndexC;
            }
        }
        lastIndexC = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for (int i = s.length() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == c) {
                lastIndexC = i;
            } else if (lastIndexC - i < ans[i]) {
                ans[i] = lastIndexC - i;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
```
