* Time: 2N
* Space: N

###Idea
Initialize an array of size maxSize. Use a pointer top to indicate current stack top.
### Code
```
class CustomStack {

    int[] stack;
    int top;
    int maxSize;

    public CustomStack(int maxSize) {
        stack = new int[maxSize];
        top = -1;
        this.maxSize = maxSize;
    }

    public void push(int x) {
        if (top < this.maxSize - 1) {
            stack[++top] = x;
        }
    }

    public int pop() {
        return top == -1 ? -1 : stack[top--];
    }

    public void increment(int k, int val) {
        for (int i = 0; i < k && i <= top; i++) {
            stack[i] += val;
        }
    }
}
```
Complexity:
* Time: push/pop O(1), inc O(K)
* Space: O(N)

### Idea
Use one stack. Push both number and string. When meets ']', pop and calculate. Always push the results back to the stack. If the next peek is a string, append to it and put it at the top.
### Code
```
class Solution {
    public String decodeString(String s) {

        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();
        Stack<String> stack = new Stack<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i ++) {
            char c = s.charAt(i);
            if (c >= '0' && c <= '9') {
                int end = i;
                while (end < s.length() && s.charAt(end) >= '0' && s.charAt(end) <= '9') {
                    end ++;
                }
                stack.push(s.substring(i, end));
                i = end - 1;
            } else if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') {
                int end = i;
                while (end < s.length() && s.charAt(end) >= 'a' && s.charAt(end) <= 'z') {
                    end ++;
                }
                if (!stack.isEmpty() && isLetterSeq(stack.peek())) {
                    stack.push(stack.pop() + s.substring(i, end));
                } else {
                    stack.push(s.substring(i, end));
                }
                i = end - 1;
            } else if (c == '[') {
                continue;
            } else if (c == ']') {
                String top = stack.pop();
                int count = Integer.valueOf(stack.pop());
                String cur = "";
                for (int j = 0; j < count; j ++) {
                    cur += top;
                }
                if (!stack.isEmpty() && isLetterSeq(stack.peek())) {
                    stack.push(stack.pop() + cur);
                } else {
                    stack.push(cur);
                }
            }
        }
        return stack.pop();
    }

    private boolean isLetterSeq(String s) {
        if (s.charAt(0) >= 'a' && s.charAt(0) <= 'z') {
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```
### Complexity
* time: 2N
* space: N

