## Idea
Iterate through the number array backwards. Add each element to k, remove the last digit from k and add it to the list.

## Code
```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> addToArrayForm(int[] num, int k) {
        List<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = num.length-1; i >= 0; i--) {
            k += num[i];
            list.add(k % 10);
            k /= 10;
        }
        while (k > 0) {
            list.add(k % 10);
            k /= 10;
        }
        Collections.reverse(list);
        return list;
    }
}
```

## Complexity
Time: O(n)
Space: O(n)

## Idea
Iterate through the string for 3 times. Locate all occurrences of c in the first iteration. Update distance based on distance on the left side in the second iteration and update distance based on distance on the right side in the third iteration.

## Code
```
class Solution {
    public int[] shortestToChar(String s, char c) {
        char[] str = s.toCharArray();
        int[] ans = new int[str.length];
        Arrays.fill(ans, Integer.MAX_VALUE);
        for (int i = 0; i < str.length; i++) {
            if (str[i] == c) {
                ans[i] = 0;
            }
        }
        
        for (int i = 0; i < str.length - 1; i++) {
            if (ans[i] != Integer.MAX_VALUE) {
                ans[i+1] = Math.min(ans[i] + 1, ans[i+1]);
            }
        }
        
        for (int i = str.length-1; i > 0; i--) {
            if (ans[i] != Integer.MAX_VALUE) {
                ans[i-1] = Math.min(ans[i] + 1, ans[i-1]);
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
```

## Complexity
Time: O(n)
Space: O(n)

## Idea
Store the element in an array and use an int variable to represent the actual size.

## Code
```
class CustomStack {
    int[] arr;
    int cur = 0;
    
    public CustomStack(int maxSize) {
        arr = new int[maxSize];        
    }
    
    public void push(int x) {
        if (cur < arr.length) {
            arr[cur++] = x;
        }
    }
    
    public int pop() {
        if (cur == 0) {
            return -1;
        }
        return arr[--cur];
    }
    
    public void increment(int k, int val) {
        for (int i = 0; i < Math.min(k, cur); i++) {
            arr[i] += val;
        }
    }
}
```

## Complexity
Time: push: O(1); pop: O(1); increment: O(min(k, cur))
Space: O(maxSize)

## Idea
Use a queue and delegate the nested encoded string to recursion
Use a int variable to store k and delegate decoding to recursion when there is a '[', and a ']' indicates that the job is done and should continue.

## Code
```
class Solution {
    public String decodeString(String s) {
        char[] str = s.toCharArray();
        Queue<Character> q = new LinkedList<>();
        for (char c : str) {
            q.add(c);
        }
        return process(q);
    }
    
    public String process(Queue<Character> q) {
        int num = 0;
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        while (!q.isEmpty()) {
            char c = q.poll();
            if (Character.isDigit(c)) {
                num *= 10;
                num += c - '0';
            }
            else if (c == '[') {
                String s = process(q);
                for (int i = 0; i < num; i++) {
                    sb.append(s);
                }
                num = 0;
            }
            else if (c == ']') {
                break;
            }
            else {
                sb.append(c);
            }
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
}
```

## Complexity
Time: O(n)
Space: O(n)

