### Idea
Let carry = k; Add k with each digit of num form right to left, 
put units digit into res, update carry 
reverse res

### Code
```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> addToArrayForm(int[] num, int k) {
        int i = num.length - 1;
        int carry = k;
        List<Integer> res = new ArrayList<>();
        
        while (i >= 0 || carry > 0) {
            if (i >= 0) {
                carry += num[i];
            }
            res.add(carry % 10);
            carry /= 10;
            i--;
        }
        Collections.reverse(res);
        return res;
    }
}
```

### Complexity
Time: O(N)  N refers to the length of num. (reach each element once) 
Space: O(1)  (no extra space except result)

## Idea
Two-pass: 
1st left to right, find shortest distant to character on left.
2nd right to left, find shortest distant to character on right, and pick shorter one.

## Code

```
class Solution {
    public int[] shortestToChar(String s, char c) {
        int n = s.length();
        int position = -n;
        int[] res = new int[n];
        
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == c) {
                position = i;   
            }
            res[i] = i - position;
            System.out.print(res[i]);
        }
        System.out.print(" ");
        for (int i = position - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == c) {
                position = i;   
            }
            res[i] = Math.min(res[i], position - i);
            System.out.print(res[i]);
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```

## Complexity
Time: O(N)  N refers to the length of string. Traverse string twice
Space: O(N) extra space for output

## Idea
Use two stack: 
One intStack to store temp number k until reach to a '['
One strStack to store temp string until reach to a ']'
The peek item of strStack will record the current temp string, 
and the after-process string is after that

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public String decodeString(String s) {
        Deque<StringBuilder> strStack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        Deque<Integer> intStack = new ArrayDeque<>();

        int k = 0;
        strStack.offerFirst(new StringBuilder());
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (Character.isDigit(c)) {
                k = k * 10 + c - '0';
            }
            else if (c == '[') {
                strStack.offerFirst(new StringBuilder());
                intStack.offerFirst(k);
                k = 0;
            }
            else if (c == ']') {
                String preStr = strStack.pollFirst().toString();
                int preK = intStack.pollFirst();
                for (int i = 0; i < preK; i++) {
                    strStack.peekFirst().append(preStr);
                }
            }
            else {
                strStack.peekFirst().append(c);
            }
        }
        return strStack.pollFirst().toString();
    }
}
```
## Complexity
Time: O(N)  N refers to length of input String
Space: O(N)

